sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K624030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pYMB indicates pUC19 with ori+Pmsp1+rep. In this construct, 13-R and Y-CHAMP are ligated in the downstream of ori+Pmsp1+rep, aimed at serving as optogenetic wireless neurostimulator with OFF state (no BRET between EYFP and rLuc) as default mode. This design is made in case EYFP fusion on N-terminal of mms13 has negative effects on its folding.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Shang-Jui Tsai
